{"lemma":"عَمُودِ","slug":"عَمُودِ","root":"ع.م.د","root_slug":"ع-م-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-م-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30504"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"column, shaft, pillar, pole"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ع م د (ʕ m d). Compare Aramaic עַמּוּדָא (ʿammūḏā, “column”), Hebrew עַמּוּד (`amúd, “column”)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.muːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30504","headword_ar":"عَمُودٌ","root":"Emd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of well-known meaning, (Msb, K,) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwd","text_ar":"عَمُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) or of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayomap","text_ar":"خَيْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pole"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a tent; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaAdN","text_ar":"عِمَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a column,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pillar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a house or the like: (L:) pl. (of pauc., S, O)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomidapN","text_ar":"اَعْمِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and (of mult., S, O)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumudN","text_ar":"عُمُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and (quasi-pl. n., L) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamadN","text_ar":"عَمَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, L, Msb, K.) [The former is the primary, and more common, meaning: and hence the phrase]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu EamuwdK","text_ar":"اَهْلُ عَمُودٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumudK","text_ar":"عُمُدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamadK","text_ar":"عَمَدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or this last is not said, (L,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu EimaAdK","text_ar":"اَهْلُ عِمَادٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, A, Msb, K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people of the tent-pole"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the tent-poles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who dwell in, tents:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, Msb, K:) or the last means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people of lofty tents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of lofty structures."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarawonahaA","text_ar":"تَرَوْنَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa A@ls~am`waAti bigayori EamadK","text_ar":"خَلَقَ ا@لسَّمٰوَاتِ بِغَيْرِ عَمَدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxxi. 9 (and see also xiii. 2)], (O, L,) accord. to Ibn-'Arafeh, (O,) or Fr, (L,) means either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He created the heavens without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamad","text_ar":"عَمَد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pillars"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ye see them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and with the sight ye need not information: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He created the heavens with pillars"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamad","text_ar":"عَمَد"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that ye see not;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with invisible pillars;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (O, * L;) the pillars that are not seen being his power; or, accord. to Lth, Mount Káf, which surrounds the world [or earth]; the sky being like a cupola, whereof the extremities rest on that mountain, which is of green chrysolite, whence, it is said, results the greenness of the sky. (L.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamadK","text_ar":"عَمَدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumudK","text_ar":"عُمُدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur [civ., last verse], accord. to different readings, are pls. [or rather the former is a quasipl. n.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamuwdN","text_ar":"عَمُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Fr, L;) or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaAdN","text_ar":"عِمَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and mean ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pillars"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of fire."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, L.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supported on poles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any tent extending to a considerable length along the ground, supported on many poles."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumodapN","text_ar":"عُمْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b4-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lord, master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) of a people, or party; (S, O;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiydN","text_ar":"عَمِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, O, K;) both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lord, master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief, upon whom persons stay themselves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rely, in their affairs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to whom they betake themselves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have recourse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the pl. of the latter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumadaA='u","text_ar":"عُمَدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And (accord. to IAar, O, L, TA) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray^iys","text_ar":"رَيِيس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commander"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (so in the L, and in the copy of the K followed in the TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasiyl","text_ar":"رَسِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning, if correct, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scout,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emissary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or perhaps the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advanced guard"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (so in the O, and in the CK, and in my MS. copy of the K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of an army;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L, K;) also called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuwayor","text_ar":"زُوَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which corroborates the former explanation, being syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray^iys","text_ar":"رَيِيس"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (L, TA; [in the O written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawiyr","text_ar":"زَوِير"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaAdN","text_ar":"عِمَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumodapN","text_ar":"عُمْدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2153},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumodaAnN","text_ar":"عُمْدَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, L, K.) ―         -b5-  Also, [from the same word in the first of the senses expl. above,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A staff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A weapon made of iron, with which one beats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strikes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rod of iron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of mace;"},{"kind":"text","text":"app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rod of iron with a ball of the same metal at the head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"I have heard this appellation applied to the kind of weapon which I have mentioned in an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAriqu","text_ar":"طَوَارِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAriqapN","text_ar":"طَارِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.; and it is vulgarly said, in Egypt, to have been used by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fidaAwiy~ap","text_ar":"فِدَاوِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", the sect called in our histories of the Crusades “ the Assassins: ”] pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomidapN","text_ar":"اَعْمِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) ―         -b7-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bar of iron,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any metal."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A perpendicular."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slender and lofty mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuqaAbu tabiyDu","text_ar":"العُقَابُ تَبِيضُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY raA^osi EamuwdK","text_ar":"فِى رَاْسِ عَمُودٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The eagle lays her eggs in the top of a slender and lofty mountain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu","text_ar":"عَمُودُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albiy^ori","text_ar":"البِيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Each of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two upright supports"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAy^imataAni","text_ar":"قَايِمَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAmataAni","text_ar":"قَامَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"placed the horizontal cross-piece of wood whereto is suspended"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the great pulley"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAlap","text_ar":"مَحَالَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the well:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) [both together being termed the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamuwdaAni","text_ar":"عَمُودَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA A@sotaqal~ato rajafa AlEamuwdaAno"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the bucket,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~alowu","text_ar":"الدَّلْوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rises, the two upright supports of the piece of wood to which hangs the great pulley tremble"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu AlZ~aliym","text_ar":"عَمُودُ الظَّلِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Each of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two legs of the male ostrich:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) his two legs are called his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamuwdaAni","text_ar":"عَمُودَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, L, TA.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu","text_ar":"عَمُودُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aliybi","text_ar":"الصَّلِيبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The upright timber of the cross"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an appellation applied by the vulgar to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star"},{"kind":"text","text":"[e]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the tail of the constellation Delphinus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu AlmiyzaAni","text_ar":"عَمُودُ المِيزَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhiyn","text_ar":"شَاهِين"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Ahyn","text_ar":"شاهين"},{"kind":"text","text":",) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beam of the balance; the same as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minojam","text_ar":"مِنْجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except that it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwd","text_ar":"عَمُود"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is generally of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qab~aAn","text_ar":"قَبَّان"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"steelyard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu Als~ayofi","text_ar":"عَمُودُ السَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aTiybap","text_ar":"شَطِيبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uTobap","text_ar":"شُطْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", generally meaning a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ridge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but sometimes a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed line,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maton","text_ar":"مَتْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broad side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle of the broad side, of the blade"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sword,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the middle of its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maton","text_ar":"مَتْن"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending to its lower part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, O:) [the swords of the Arabs in the earlier ages being generally straight and twoedged:] and sometimes the sword had three"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomidap","text_ar":"اَعْمِدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of pauc. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamuwdN","text_ar":"عَمُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in its back, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uTub","text_ar":"شُطُب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aTaAy^ib","text_ar":"شَطَايِب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (En-Nadr, O.) ―         -b15-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu Als~inaAni","text_ar":"عَمُودُ السِّنَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ridge"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayor","text_ar":"عَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the O and in copies of the K [erroneously] written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayor","text_ar":"غَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising along the middle of the spear-head, between its two cutting sides."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, O, L, K. *) ―         -b16-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu AlbaToni","text_ar":"عَمُودُ البَطْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The back;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, O, L, K;) because it supports the belly: (Mgh, O, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vein"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiroq","text_ar":"عِرْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing resembling a vein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending from the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhaAbap","text_ar":"رُهَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower extremity of the sternum"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a little below the navel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the middle whereof the belly of the sheep or goat is cut open;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says Lth: (O, L:) or, accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vein extending from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rhAbp","text_ar":"رهابة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the navel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) They said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmalahu EalaY Eamuwdi baTonihi","text_ar":"حمَلَهُ عَلَى عَمُودِ بَطْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He carried it on his back:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L:) or, in the opinion of A'Obeyd, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trouble, and fatigue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether upon his back or not. (O, L.) ―         -b17-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu Alkabidi","text_ar":"عَمُودُ الكَبِدِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rising thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu$orifu","text_ar":"المُشْرِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the longitudinal ligament"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the middle of the liver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj in his “ Khalk el-Insán: ”) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain vein that irrigates the liver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamuwdaA Alkabidi","text_ar":"عَمُودَا الكَبِدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two large veins, on the right and left of the navel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, O, L.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a fulaAnFA laxaArijN Eamuwdu","text_ar":"اـِنَّ فُلَانًا لَخَارِجٌ عَمُودُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabidihi mina AljuwEi","text_ar":"كَبِدِهِ مِنَ الجُوعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily such a one has his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Emwd","text_ar":"عمود"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his liver coming forth in consequence of hunger"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwduhu mino kabidihi","text_ar":"عَمُودُهُ مِنْ كَبِدِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Emwd","text_ar":"عمود"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his liver"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (L, TA;) and some say that by his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Emwd","text_ar":"عمود"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this saying is meant what here next follows. (TA.) ―         -b18-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu Als~aHori","text_ar":"عَمُودُ السَّحْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watiyn","text_ar":"وَتِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aorta,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though it were considered as the support of the lungs]. (O, K.) ―         -b19-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu AlA^u*uni","text_ar":"عَمُودُ الاُذُنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The main part, and support, of the ear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L, K, TA: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawAmuhA","text_ar":"قَوامُها"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiwaAmuhaA","text_ar":"قِوَامُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the round part which is above the lobe."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b20-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu Alqalobi","text_ar":"عَمُودُ القَلْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The middle of the heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lengthwise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain vein that irrigates it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijoEalo *`lika fiY Eamuwdi qalobika","text_ar":"اِجْعَلْ ذٰلِكَ فِى عَمُودِ قَلْبِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Put thou that in the middle of thy heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b21-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu All~isaAni","text_ar":"عَمُودُ اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The middle of the tongue, lengthwise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b22-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu","text_ar":"عَمُودُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The text of the book:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa ma*okuwrN fiY Eamuwdi AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"هُوَ مَذْكُورٌ فِى عَمُودِ الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is mentioned in the text of the book"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b23-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu AlS~uboHi","text_ar":"عَمُودُ الصُّبْحِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bright gleam of dawn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dawn that rises and spreads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, Msb, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filling the horizon with its whiteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajorN","text_ar":"فَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [app. thus called as being likened to a tent, or long tent:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is the second,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajor","text_ar":"فَجْر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rises after the first,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"false,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fjr","text_ar":"فجر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has disappeared; and with its rising, the day commences, and everything by which the fast would be broken becomes forbidden to the faster."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajorN","text_ar":"فَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTaEa","text_ar":"سَطَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu AlS~uboHi","text_ar":"عَمُودُ الصُّبْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, L,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba AlS~uboHu biEamuwdihi","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ الصُّبْحُ بِعَمُودِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba Alfajoru biEamuwdihi","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ الفَجْرُ بِعَمُودِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bright gleam of dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose and spread."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b24-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu AlA_iEoSaAri","text_ar":"عَمُودُ الاـِعْصَارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which rises into the sky,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extends along the surface of the earth, in consequence of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEoSaAr","text_ar":"اـِعْصَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (O, L.) ―         -b25-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu AlHusoni","text_ar":"عَمُودُ الحُسْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tallness of stature."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mlA^","text_ar":"ملا"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b26-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwdu Aln~awaY","text_ar":"عَمُودُ النَّوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The state of distance, from their friends, in which travellers continue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b27-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^irapu AlEamuwdi","text_ar":"دَايِرَةُ العَمُودِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The curl of the hair"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which we term a feather"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on a horse's neck, in the places of the collar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is approved by the Arabs. (L.) ―         -b28-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaqaAmuwA EalaY Eamuwdi raA^oyihimo","text_ar":"اِسْتَقَامُوا عَلَى عَمُودِ رَاْيِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They continued in the course upon which they placed reliance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)       -A2-  Also, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamuwdN","text_ar":"عَمُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to the O and K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiydN","text_ar":"عَمِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to the TA [agreeably with an explanation of the latter in the L],)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Affected with vehement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intense, grief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","O","L","Lth","A","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}